@startuml AC-03_Client_Supplied_Price

title AC-03 — Client-Supplied Unit Price Bypasses Server-Side Catalog Validation\nSTRIDE: Tampering | Severity: Critical | Mitigation: M-03

left to right direction

skinparam usecase {
  BackgroundColor<< abuse >> #FFCCCC
  BorderColor<< abuse >> #CC0000
  FontColor<< abuse >> #CC0000
  BackgroundColor<< normal >> #DDEEFF
  BorderColor<< normal >> #336699
}
skinparam actorBackgroundColor #EEF
skinparam actorBorderColor #336699
skinparam noteFontSize 10

actor "Customer\n(Legitimate)" as customer #DDEEFF
actor "Malicious Customer" as attacker #FFCCCC

rectangle "VendNet System" {
  usecase "Purchase Product at\nCatalog Price" as UC3 << normal >>
  usecase "Intercept POST /sales\nRequest (Burp Suite)" as AC3a << abuse >>
  usecase "Submit Modified unitPrice\n(e.g., £0.01)" as AC3 << abuse >>
  usecase "Purchase High-Value Products\nat Near-Zero Cost" as AC3b << abuse >>
}

customer --> UC3

attacker --> AC3a
AC3a ..> AC3   : <<extends>>
AC3 ..> UC3    : <<threatens>>
AC3 ..> AC3b   : <<extends>>

note right of AC3
  **Preconditions:**
  • Valid Customer-scoped JWT
  • POST /sales body contains
    user-controllable unitPrice field
  • P3 uses client-supplied unitPrice
    instead of server-side catalog lookup
  • No cross-validation at commit time
end note

note right of AC3b
  **Impact:**
  Integrity: Sale records contain false
  UnitPrice values; inventory depleted
  without corresponding revenue
  Financial: direct revenue loss per
  transaction, scalable across all products
  Business: corrupted financial reports,
  fraud liability
end note

note bottom of attacker
  **Attack vector (intercepting proxy):**
  Original: {"productId":"prod-123","unitPrice":2.50}
  Modified: {"productId":"prod-123","unitPrice":0.01}
end note

@enduml
